          • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

            I can understand the tactics against Barcelona given the dynamic of a two-legged tie (especially if you enter the 2nd leg with a good result), the fact Barca have/had a couple of defenders who make mistakes on the ball when pressured, the fact Barca can also struggle creatively against 'in numbers' type defending and well, it nearly worked. But here? Pointless. City aren't a team you can just hope to defend against for 90 minutes and this was obviously not a two-legged affair. Defending deep and hitting on the counter is a valid tactic but Hazard should be on the wing with Morata up front otherwise you can't utilize that game-plan fully and that is really what we saw. It was a "let's take a 0-0/0-1 back to the Bridge" type of performance. Strange really but all is not well in the Chelsea camp, Conte doesn't trust Morata for whatever reason(s), Giroud was bought as a backup and now it seems Antonio likes this interchange false-9 front-3 setup against every opposition.
